# Claims and Critiques Structure

Arguments in this debate use **explicit numbered claims and critiques**.

Claims are labeled:

C1, C2, C3, ...

Critiques are labeled:

K1, K2, K3, ...

Critiques typically target specific claims.

Example:

K2: Claim C1 assumes inflation persistence without wage evidence.

During revision, agents must explicitly respond to critiques by either:

• **ACCEPTING** them (if they reveal a real flaw)
• **REJECTING** them (if they do not materially affect the thesis)

Use this structure when evaluating reasoning quality.

